OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFormer BBC political editor
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FStephen Grimason dies      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The former BBC News NI political editor
OL,6, Stephen Grimason, who broke the news of
OL,7, the 1998 Good Friday Agreement, has    
OL,8, died aged 67 after a long illness.     
OL,10,FAcross three decades in journalism, Mr 
OL,11,FGrimason's career saw him report on    
OL,12,Fsome of the darkest, most notorious    
OL,13,Fmoments of Northern Ireland's Troubles.
OL,15,FBut he is possibly best known for his  
OL,16,Freporting of the peace deal which      
OL,17,Fhelped to end the Troubles.            
OL,19,F"I have it in my hand," he declared on 
OL,20,Ftelevision, while holding the document.
